---
import { Media } from 'accessible-astro-components'
import ContentMedia from '../components/ContentMedia.astro'
import Counter from '../components/Counter.astro'
import Feature from '../components/Feature.astro'
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro'
import DefaultLayout from '../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
---

<DefaultLayout>
  <Hero />

  <section class="my-56" id="main-content">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="about" class="text-6xl">About SoCraTes Canada</h2>

      <div class="mt-20 grid grid-cols-1 gap-12 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4">
        <Counter count="25" title="Participants" sub="who care about quality" />
        <Counter count="48" title="Hours" sub="in a cabin" />
        <Counter count="82" title="Mashmallows" sub="waiting to be grilled" />
        <Counter count="167+" title="Ideas" sub="to be shared" />
      </div>

      <div class="space-content mt-20 text-lg">
        <p>
          SoCraTes stands for <strong>So</strong>ftware <strong>Cra</strong>ft and <strong>Tes</strong>ting. It's a
          2-day <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f8kMII_N_OY" target="_blank" class="italic"
            >Open-Space unconference</a
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          You know all the insightful discussions that happen in the hallway of a conference? That's what an
          <em>unconference</em> is! We bring 25 passionate people offsite for 2 days and make it easy for sessions to happen.
          Each participant is also a potential speaker. At the end of this "retreat", everyone goes back home with new ideas,
          perspectives, and connections.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-20 flex flex-col gap-12 text-xl">
        <ContentMedia imgSrc="/marketplace.jpg" reverseImg>
          <h3>It starts with the Marketplace</h3>
          <p>
            Before each work session, we gather in the main lodge to propose and select the topics we want to discuss.
          </p>
          <p>
            Any participant can propose a topic they would like to teach or learn about. Pick a time and place, present
            your session to the group, and voil√†!
          </p>
        </ContentMedia><ContentMedia imgSrc="/roundtable-session.webp">
          <h3>Work sessions</h3>
          <p>
            For a few hours, participants gather in small groups to discuss the topics they are interested in. It's a
            great way to learn from others, share your knowledge, and get feedback on your ideas.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most sessions will look like roundtable discussions. Although, some may propose hands-on coding or other
            workshops.
          </p>
        </ContentMedia>
        <ContentMedia imgSrc="/meals.jpeg" reverseImg>
          <h3>Enjoying meals</h3>
          <p>
            We spend lunch and dinner together in the main lodge. It's a great time to continue the discussions, or to
            relax and enjoy the Canadian experience.
          </p>
          <p>Meals are prepared and served by a local caterer.</p>
        </ContentMedia>
        <ContentMedia imgSrc="/having-fun.jpg">
          <h3>And having fun!</h3>
          <p>
            Overall, this is a retreat to learn, share, and enjoy time together. We have fun activities scheduled in the
            evenings, such as grilling marshmallows, playing board games, etc.
          </p>
          <p>It's a great opportunity to make new connections and maybe new friends!</p>
        </ContentMedia>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-20 grid grid-cols-1 gap-12 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <Feature icon="ion:people-outline" title="It's about People">
          Participants love developing high-quality, maintainable softwares. Expect creative discussions and rich
          learnings from passionate people.
        </Feature>
        <Feature icon="ion:rocket-outline" title="It's about Action">
          For 48 hours, we will share ideas in a self-organized Open Space. Expect hands-on coding sessions, roundtable
          discussions, interactive talks and more!
        </Feature>
        <Feature icon="ion:happy-outline" title="It's about Fun">
          Besides insightful work sessions, enjoy the Canadian experience: take a walk in the woods, have a beer near
          the firecamp, or just relax in the hot tub‚Ä¶
        </Feature>
      </div>

      <div class="space-content mt-20 text-lg">
        <p>
          SoCraTes Canada is the Canadian edition of a larger family. You will find other SoCraTes unconferences around
          the globe, such as:
        </p>
        <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <li><a href="https://socrates-fr.github.io/" target="_blank">SoCraTes France</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.socrates-conference.de/" target="_blank">SoCraTes Germany</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://socratesuk.org/" target="_blank">SoCraTes UK</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.socrates-conference.es/" target="_blank">SoCraTes Canaries</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://socrates-ch.org/" target="_blank">SoCraTes Switzerland</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://socratesbe.org/" target="_blank">SoCraTes BE</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.socrates-conference.it/" target="_blank">SoCraTes IT</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://socrates-conference.at/" target="_blank">SoCraTes Austria</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.socrates-conference.cl/" target="_blank">SoCraTes Chile</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.codefreeze.fi/" target="_blank">Code Freeze</a></li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://mozaicworks.com/product/i-t-a-k-e-unconference" target="_blank">I.T.A.K.E Unconference</a>
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://scunconf.com/" target="_blank">Software Crafters Unconference</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="space-content mt-20 text-lg">
        <div class="timeline-container">
          <p class="mb-10">This won't be our first drill. We had previous editions under our belt:</p>

          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-slide">
              <div class="slide-top font-bold">March 2020</div>
              <div class="slide-bottom">
                <div>First winter edition</div>

                <Media class="rounded-lg" src="/team-socrates-2020.jpg" />
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-slide">
              <div class="slide-top font-bold">October 2023</div>
              <div class="slide-bottom">
                <div>Second edition (Fall colors)</div>
                <Media class="rounded-lg" src="/team-socrates-2023.jpg" />
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-slide">
              <div class="slide-top font-bold">October 2024</div>
              <div class="slide-bottom">
                <div>Third edition, with you?</div>
                <Media class="rounded-lg" src="/team-socrates-2024.jpg" />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="my-40">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="venue" class="text-6xl">Discover the Selenia Lodge</h2>
          <div class="space-content mt-20 text-lg">
            <p>
              The 2024 edition will take place at <a href="https://www.selenialodge.com/" target="_blank"
                >the Selenia Lodge</a
              >, a hidden treasure of the Laurentides.
            </p>
            <iframe
              src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2772.0432357878117!2d-74.75409798324107!3d45.99036599958369!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4ccfa7a15a610e73%3A0xfb5d3bca04c5793a!2sSelenia%20Lodge!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sca!4v1708366428839!5m2!1sfr!2sca"
              width="600"
              height="450"
              style="border:0; margin: 1.5rem auto 0;"
              allowfullscreen=""
              loading="lazy"
              referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe>
            <p>
              It's a wonderful place to relax, work, and have fun. The lodge is located 1h45 car drive away from
              Montreal, to the North. It's a perfect place to enjoy the Canadian fall colors in early October üçÅ
            </p>
            <p>
              If you need help to get there, we facilitate <a
                href="https://github.com/socrates-ca/socrates-ca.github.io/wiki/CarSharing">Car Sharing</a
              > between participants.
            </p>
            <ContentMedia imgSrc="/selenia-lodge.jpg">
              <p>
                One big central lodge is reserved for our work sessions and meals. This is where we spend most of our
                day.
              </p>
              <p>We rest in cabins that are spread around the main lodge.</p>
              <p>
                Participants share a cabin with 1 to 3 other participants. Each participant has their individual
                bedroom.
              </p>
              <p>The lodge is also equiped with fire places and hot tubs, to relax at the end of the day üî•</p>
            </ContentMedia>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="my-40">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="schedule" class="text-6xl">The Agenda</h2>

          <div class="space-content mt-20 text-lg">
            <p>
              The conference starts on <strong>Friday 4th at 2pm</strong> and ends on <strong>Sunday 6th at 2pm</strong
              >.
            </p>
            <p>
              The exact Agenda is made by the participants, on the spot. It's an Open Space, so <a
                href="http://unconference.net/unconferencing-how-to-prepare-to-attend-an-unconference/"
                target="_blank">it's up to you</a
              > to propose a session, or to join one.
            </p>
            <p>
              Facilitation will be in English. However, it will be possible to run sessions in other languages (eg.
              French).
            </p>
            <p>
              In the evenings, participants are free to chill as they like: listening to music in the hot tub,
              continuing the discussions around the fire pit, playing pool or board games, or even live-hacking programs
              solo or together‚Ä¶ you choose!
            </p>
            <p>Here is a rough idea of how the unconference would look like, time-wise:</p>
          </div>

